            "creation_date": 1429470955,
            "body": "<p>Remember that e!=é and u00e9=é, this would return true :<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>System.out.println(\"\\u00e9\" == (\"é\"));//Notice é instead of e\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>Note that even if this will work in that case because we compare character literal (as @Pshemo explained in comments), make sure you compare longer strings with <code>.equals<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734609,
            "question_id": 29734552,
            "last_edit_date": 1429472586
        },
        {
            "owner": {
                "profile_image": "https://i.sstatic.net/Fp4Pm.jpg?s=256",
                "account_id": 1085259,
                "user_type": "registered",
                "user_id": 1081110,
                "link": "https://stackoverflow.com/users/1081110/dawood-ibn-kareem",
