                "display_name": "Dawood ibn Kareem"
            },
            "content_license": "CC BY-SA 3.0",
            "score": 2,
            "is_accepted": true,
            "last_activity_date": 1429471464,
            "creation_date": 1429471464,
            "body": "<p>The reason for the unexpected output is the extra semi-colon after the first <code>if<\/code>.<\/p>\n\n<p>Currently, you have<\/p>\n\n<pre><code>if(\"\\u00e9\" == letterToGet.toLowerCase()); {\n    letterToGet = \"SPECIALACCTAIGUESPECIAL\";\n}\n<\/code><\/pre>\n\n<p>in which the assignment to <code>letterToGet<\/code> is outside of the scope of the <code>if<\/code>, so it will run, regardless of the value of <code>letterToGet<\/code>.<\/p>\n",
            "answer_id": 29734728,
            "question_id": 29734552
        }
